        "id": 1940035,
        "name": "Nicos Neocleous",
        "username": "Nicos_Neocleous",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/ecd19e/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2016-05-29T14:37:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p><strong>1959 Chambolle-Musigny</strong></p>\n<p>With Sunday luncheon, I felt that a properly mature (not 1993) red burgundy would be appealing.  This wine was bottled by London wine merchants Corney &amp; Barrow Limited.  The plain label, with the Royal Warrant, belies the hopefully complex contents.  A deep strawberry red with a light red rim.  The nose gives me sweet raspberry and strawberry jam, with hints of spices.  The mouthfeel is savoury and fresh, with a soft red fruit compote mid palate and a long lingering length.  Fully mature if you love old school Burgundy.  The last bottle of this wine that I shared about 5 years ago was bigger, bolder and even slightly tannic.</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i87.photobucket.com/albums/k138/nicosneocleous/IMG_9791_zps8ddslysx.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i87.photobucket.com/albums/k138/nicosneocleous/IMG_9792_zpsf243w2yv.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i87.photobucket.com/albums/k138/nicosneocleous/IMG_9793_zpslpyex1ga.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i87.photobucket.com/albums/k138/nicosneocleous/IMG_9794_zpsb1ygrto4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"http://i87.photobucket.com/albums/k138/nicosneocleous/IMG_9795_zpsag19uza4.jpg\" alt=\"\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
